      Originating from Thailand (formerly Siam), this breed has a rich history, often linked to royalty. They are highly
      social, vocal, and intelligent cats, often forming strong bonds with their owners. Their short coat features a
      color-point pattern, with common colors including seal, chocolate, blue, and lilac. Siamese typically weigh 6-14
      pounds
      and live 10-15 years. They require moderate grooming and plenty of interaction.</p>
  </div>

